title: Did Colleen Cypernik donate $25,000 to the Asata Shakur tribute group?
subtitle: This group was named after the member of the Black Liberation Army, who was convicted of the murder of a State soldier and fled to Cuba.
author: Arturo Garcia
vclaim: Colin Kaybernik donated $25,000 to an activist group named Asata Shakur, who was convicted of the murder of a police officer.
